/ service
%section#service.section-padding
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-4.col-sm-4
        %h2.ser-title Elder Care Homes
        %hr.botm-line/
        %p Homes, in varying sizes and styles, may be the best choice for people with illnesses or physical or mental limitations that require monitoring and care from medical professionals. To find the best fit, take the time and effort to compare a few facilities as to quality of care as well as personal preferences such as location, size, and resident characteristics.

      .col-md-4.col-sm-4
        .service-info
          .icon
            %i.fa.fa-stethoscope
          .icon-info
            %h4 24 Hour Support
            %p Residents have 24-hour access to trained staff, so they can be continuously monitored for medical needs and can receive help with the activities of daily living.
        .service-info
          .icon
            %i.fa.fa-heartbeat
          .icon-info
            %h4 Monitored Care
            %p Residents will be monitored closely throughout their stay at the Nursing Home facility. They typically have a set of dedicated professionals to keep them on scheduled medication if needed and help them get the movement they need.

      .col-md-4.col-sm-4
        .service-info
          .icon
            %i.fa.fa-user-md
          .icon-info
            %h4 Service Options
            %p There are two levels of adult home care. In a skilled nursing facility (SNF), residents are under the 24-hour care of licensed or registered nursing staff, while in an intermediate care facility residents are cared for by certified nursing assistants.
        .service-info
          .icon
            %i.fa.fa-medkit
          .icon-info
            %h4 Healthcare Cost
            %p Adult Home facilities assess fees on a daily basis. If necessary, additional services and supplies may be added to a patientâ€™s bill. Prices vary based on location and level of assistance the patient will need.

